+After a review completes for a patch agent, the controller appends
+`work-leaf: Is this feature done? yes/no` to that patch-agent chat. A `yes` or `y` answer records the
+feature as closed without resuming the backend agent. A `no` or `n` answer records the feature as
+reopened without resuming the backend agent, so the next message can continue the same patch-agent
+session. Any other reply records the reopen marker and sends the reply as the next agent prompt. When
+multiple review cycles reuse the same patch-agent chat, repeated close or reopen markers receive
+numeric suffixes so every prompt acknowledgement remains visible in the transcript.
+
